{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἁφή</b>, ἡ, <br /> (ἅπτω) <b>lighting, kindling,</b> περὶ λύχνων ἁφάς about lamp-<b>lighting</b> time, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.215, compare “PTeb.” 88.12 (2nd c.BC), 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 11.33, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 19.31, 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 12.526c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> (ἅπτομαι) <b>touch,</b> ἐπώνυμον δὲ τῶν Διὸς γέννημ᾽ ἁφῶν (Wieseler for γεννημάτων) τέξεις.. Ἔπαφον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 850. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>sense of touch,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 523e, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1118b1, “de An.” 424a12; ἀκριβεστάτην.. τῶν αἰσθήσεων τὴν ἁφήν [prev. author] “HA” 494b16; ἡ ἁφὴ ἐν ταῖς αἰσθήσεσι παρέσπαρται 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Salt.” 70. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>touch of the harp-strings,</b> <i>metaphorically</i>, ἐμμελοῦς ἁφῆς καὶ κρούσεως[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pericles” 15; οὐχὶ συμφώνους ἁφάς 4th-3rd c.BC: Damoxenus Comicus 2.42. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <b>grip,</b> in wrestling, etc., ἁφὴν ἐνδιδόναι αὑτοῦ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.86f: _metaphorically_, τοῖς ἀφληταῖς τῆς λέξεως ἰσχυρὰς τὰς ἁ. προσεῖναι δεῖ καὶ ἀφύκτους τὰς λαβάς 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Demosthene” 18; ἁφὰς ἔχει καὶ τόνους ἰσχυρούς [prev. author] “Lys.” 13\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; ἁ. εἶχεν ἡ συνδιαίτησις ἄφυκτον, of [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Cleopatra, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Antonius” 27. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> 